---
import Base from '../../layouts/Base.astro';
---
<Base title="SocialProof for Acupuncturists — Testimonials That Build Patient Trust | SocialProof" description="SocialProof helps acupuncturists collect and display patient testimonials on their website. Send a link, get a testimonial, embed it — free forever for 1 widget.">
  <main class="for-page">
    <section class="hero">
      <div class="badge">For Acupuncturists</div>
      <h1>New Patients Trust Outcomes — Let Your Results Speak</h1>
      <p class="subhead">People considering acupuncture are often skeptical — or nervous. Authentic testimonials from your real patients showing real results are the single most effective way to convert curious visitors into first-time appointments.</p>
      <div class="cta-group">
        <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="btn-primary">Start free — no credit card</a>
        <a href="/for" class="btn-secondary">See all industries →</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="pain">
      <h2>The Trust Barrier in Integrative Health</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>New patients are often trying acupuncture for the first time — they need reassurance it works</li>
        <li>They search for conditions: "acupuncture for back pain", "acupuncture for fertility" — testimonials matching their condition convert</li>
        <li>Privacy concerns mean patients hesitate to leave public Google reviews about sensitive health matters</li>
        <li>A plain website with no social proof looks no different from a practitioner who just graduated</li>
      </ul>
    </section>

    <section class="solution">
      <h2>How SocialProof Works for Acupuncturists</h2>
      <ol>
        <li><strong>Set up your collect link</strong> — private, HIPAA-friendly testimonial collection (no diagnosis details required)</li>
        <li><strong>Send after a patient achieves a milestone</strong> — reduced pain, better sleep, successful fertility outcome</li>
        <li><strong>Patients share anonymously if they prefer</strong> — they can submit as "Patient in Seattle" rather than full name</li>
        <li><strong>Approve and embed</strong> — display on your website with one script tag</li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <section class="social-proof-for-sp">
      <h2>What Acupuncturists Say About SocialProof</h2>
      <blockquote>
        <p>"My patients who struggled with chronic pain and finally found relief through acupuncture are my most passionate advocates. SocialProof made it easy to capture those stories — and now new patients tell me they booked because of what they read."</p>
        <cite>— Licensed acupuncturist, Portland OR</cite>
      </blockquote>
      <blockquote>
        <p>"People are often skeptical about acupuncture. Having 25+ testimonials from real patients describing real results changed my conversion rate completely."</p>
        <cite>— Integrative health practice, Boston MA</cite>
      </blockquote>
    </section>

    <section class="use-cases">
      <h2>Built for Acupuncture Practices of All Sizes</h2>
      <div class="grid-3">
        <div class="card"><strong>Solo practitioners</strong><p>Your reputation is everything. Build a library of patient outcomes that works as your most powerful marketing tool.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><strong>Wellness clinics</strong><p>Collect testimonials across multiple practitioners and service types. Show the breadth of your practice's impact.</p></div>
        <div class="card"><strong>Fertility & specialty focus</strong><p>Patients searching for acupuncture for specific conditions need targeted social proof. Organize testimonials by treatment area.</p></div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="faq">
      <h2>Common Questions</h2>
      <details>
        <summary>Can patients submit anonymously?</summary>
        <p>Yes. Patients can submit using their first name only, a pseudonym, or "Anonymous Patient." You approve every testimonial before it goes live, so you control what's displayed.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Is this HIPAA compliant?</summary>
        <p>SocialProof collects voluntary testimonials — not medical records or health data. Patients choose what to share. We recommend not asking patients to include specific diagnoses in public testimonials.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What does it cost?</summary>
        <p>Free forever for 1 active widget. Upgrade to Pro ($19/mo) for multiple widgets, custom branding, and advanced filtering.</p>
      </details>
    </section>

    <section class="final-cta">
      <h2>Turn Patient Outcomes Into New Patient Bookings</h2>
      <p>Set up your testimonial widget in minutes. Free forever for 1 active widget.</p>
      <a href="https://app.socialproof.dev/signup" class="btn-primary">Get started free</a>
    </section>
  </main>

